                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#decimal"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/National_implementations/NR/Common#TimingPoint"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/National_implementations/NR/Common#TrafficFlow"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Represents a path through a rail node (operational locality, station) by connecting two lines of way.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>RailNodePath</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/National_implementations/NR/Common#SignallingEquivalentUnit -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/National_implementations/NR/Common#SignallingEquivalentUnit">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfigurationProperty"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/National_implementations/NR/Common#rate"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#decimal"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:comment>Signalling Equivalent Unit (SEU) is a way of estimating the size of a signalling project; This determines if  a piece of equipment is counted as an SEU or part of one.
E.g. a signal &amp;amp; a point are 1 SEU each regardless complexity and components.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>rate
The SEU rate.
Allows weighting the cost of the asset for accounting purposes.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>SignallingEquivalentUnit</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/National_implementations/NR/Common#SubTimingPoint -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/National_implementations/NR/Common#SubTimingPoint">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/National_implementations/NR/Common#TimingPoint"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/National_implementations/NR/Common#hasParentTimingPoint"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/National_implementations/NR/Common#TimingPoint"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:comment>The sub-TIPLOC gives more detail for a given TIPLOC code (such as where a line code is used with a TIPLOC code to define the path of a timetabled service)</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>SubTimingPoint</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/National_implementations/NR/Common#TimingPoint -->

