    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Flank_protection#FlankProtection -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Flank_protection#FlankProtection">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Flank_protection#SectionsForFlankProtection"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Flank protection prevents rolling stock from unintentionally entering the train&apos;s route body.
Flank protection is given when selected elements, notably points, prove a given state.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>remote
When flank protection measure is remote, the remote flank protection measure is given. 
de-DE: Fernschutz. Der Flankenschutz wird durch das n&amp;#228;chste Flankenschutzelement hergestellt. (Ersatzschutzma&amp;#223;nahme)</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>FlankProtection</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Flank_protection#SectionsForFlankProtection -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Flank_protection#SectionsForFlankProtection">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <rdfs:comment>List of TVP sections required for flank protection of a given route.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>SectionsForFlankProtection</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingArea -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingArea">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingAreaUiElement"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingZone"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingZoneLimit"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingZoneRelation"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozAssetRelation"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Part of the interlocking area that a local operator can control on site, notably for directing shunting movements. The procedure of handing over control between signaller and local operator is supported by switches, keys and indicators on a local operating device.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>LocalOperatingArea</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingAreaUiElement -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingAreaUiElement">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#affectsLocalOperatingZone"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingZone"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#appliesToLocalOperationUiElement_LocalOperatingAreaUiElement"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Local_operation_devices#LocalOperationUiElement"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#hasFunctionType_LocalOperatingAreaUiElement"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingZone"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingZoneLimit"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingZoneRelation"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozAssetRelation"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Associates a button, switch or pull cord with a given function allowing local staff to interact with a local operating zone.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>LocalOperatingAreaUiElement</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingZone -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingZone">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingZoneLimit"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingZoneRelation"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozAssetRelation"/>
        <rdfs:comment>A local operating area consists of at least one local operating zone. The zone groups elements that can be worked locally. 
Zones can be disjoint, touch or even overlap. Adjacent zones can be independent, or can merge into a bigger zone to allow seamless shunting movement between them. Local control over the zones is taken in a given order, given by rank, e.g. 1-2-3. Handing back control is the inverse- operation, e.g. 3-2-1.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>LocalOperatingZone</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingZoneLimit -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingZoneLimit">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#isDefinedByLocationProxy"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#LocationProxy"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#isOfLocalOperatingZoneLimitType"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#limitsLocalOperatingZone"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingZone"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingZoneRelation"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozAssetRelation"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Outer limit of the local control area. 
This limit is flank protected.
The limit is represented by a signal, point or derailer</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>LocalOperatingZoneLimit</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingZoneRelation -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingZoneRelation">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#appliesToZoneA"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingZone"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#appliesToZoneB"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LocalOperatingZone"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#isOfLocalOperatingZoneRelationType"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozAssetRelation"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Informs about the relation between local operation zones A and B.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>LocalOperatingZoneRelation</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozAssetRelation -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozAssetRelation">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#controllable_LozAssetRelation"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:comment>Assigns an asset to a local operating zone.
Optionally defines the condition for taking or returning the zone from/to the signaller.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>controllable
Indicates whether the local operator has full control (true, default) or not (false) over the asset when the local operating zone is active. Applies only to signal, point and derailer.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>LozAssetRelation</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozDerailerRelation -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozDerailerRelation">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozAssetRelation"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#appliesToDerailerElement"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Point_crossing_derailer#MovableElement"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozLcDangerAreaTrackRelation"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozLevelCrossingRelation"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozPointRelation"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozReleaseInstrumentRelation"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozSignalRelation"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozTdsSectionRelation"/>
        <rdfs:label>LozDerailerRelation</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozLcDangerAreaTrackRelation -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozLcDangerAreaTrackRelation">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozAssetRelation"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#appliesToDangerAreaTrack_LozLcDangerAreaTrackRelation"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Level_crossing#DangerAreaTrack"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozLevelCrossingRelation"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozPointRelation"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozReleaseInstrumentRelation"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozSignalRelation"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozTdsSectionRelation"/>
        <rdfs:comment>The level crossing&apos;s track-related danger area is conditional to the LOZ activation. 
This allows the scenario where a level crossing across more than one track is partly under local control (in a LOZ), partly under control of the interlocking.
If the level crossing system as a whole is part of a LOZ, then use the LozLevelCrossingRelation.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>LozLcDangerAreaTrackRelation</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozLevelCrossingRelation -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozLevelCrossingRelation">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozAssetRelation"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#appliesToLevelCrossingSystem_LozLevelCrossingRelation"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Level_crossing#LevelCrossingSystem"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozPointRelation"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozReleaseInstrumentRelation"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozSignalRelation"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozTdsSectionRelation"/>
        <rdfs:label>LozLevelCrossingRelation</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozPointRelation -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozPointRelation">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozAssetRelation"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#appliesToPointElement"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Point_crossing_derailer#MovableElement"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozReleaseInstrumentRelation"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozSignalRelation"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozTdsSectionRelation"/>
        <rdfs:label>LozPointRelation</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozReleaseInstrumentRelation -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozReleaseInstrumentRelation">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozAssetRelation"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#appliesToReleaseInstrument"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Key_locks#ReleaseInstrument"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozSignalRelation"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozTdsSectionRelation"/>
        <rdfs:comment>A key release instrument for taking/handing back the local operating zone.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>needsKeyPresenceForReturn
True: The key must be locked inside the key release instrument before the local operating zone can be taken from/handed back to the signaller.

False: the interlocking doesn&apos;t check the presence of the key before taking/handing back the zone.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>LozReleaseInstrumentRelation</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozSignalRelation -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozSignalRelation">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozAssetRelation"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#appliesToSignal_LozSignalRelation"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Signal#ActiveSignal"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozTdsSectionRelation"/>
        <rdfs:label>LozSignalRelation</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozTdsSectionRelation -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozTdsSectionRelation">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Local_operating_area#LozAssetRelation"/>
        <rdfs:comment>A TDS section within the local operating zone.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>LozTdsSectionRelation</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#CompositeRoute -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#CompositeRoute">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ConditionSectionsClear"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ConflictingRoute"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#NonReplacement"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#Route"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteApproachLocking"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBody"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBodyProperty"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteCondition"/>
        <rdfs:comment>A route that is composed of two or more elementary routes. The elementary routes are commonly referred to as atomic routes or subroutes.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>CompositeRoute</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#CompoundLogicalObject -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#CompoundLogicalObject">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets#PhysicalTrackAsset"/>
        <rdfs:comment>A fa&amp;#231;ade to a system or device implementing Boolean logic. It can represent anything from a simple relay contact to complex relay circuitry or a PLC that converts high/low electric input signals from any source into Boolean true/false outputs. 
It can exchange binary i/o with the interlocking. 
Use this for ancillary equipment connected to the interlocking, e.g. bascule bridges, tunnel equipment, detectors (such as earthquake and flooding detectors). Also useful for reading inputs from field-activated level crossings.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>Description
Description of the logic.
Textual description of the field elements and Boolean relations that produce the Boolean output.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>CompoundLogicalObject</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ConditionAffectingKRI -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ConditionAffectingKRI">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ConditionAffectingRoute"/>
        <rdfs:label>ConditionAffectingKRI</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ConditionAffectingRoute -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ConditionAffectingRoute">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteCondition"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#affectsRoute_ConditionAffectingRoute"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#Route"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:comment>Condition required for the route to open, read from a compound logical object or a release instrument.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>ConditionAffectingRoute</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ConditionAffectingSignal -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ConditionAffectingSignal">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteCondition"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#affectsSignal_ConditionAffectingSignal"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Statespace#SignalAndMessage"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:comment>Condition required for the signal to show a given aspect, read from a compound logical object or a release instrument.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>ConditionAffectingSignal</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ConditionSectionsClear -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ConditionSectionsClear">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#affectsRoute_ConditionSectionsClear"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#Route"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#overrideable"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ConflictingRoute"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#NonReplacement"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#Route"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteApproachLocking"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBody"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBodyProperty"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteCondition"/>
        <rdfs:comment>TVP section(s) proven clear to open the route entry signal. This check allows to send a second train into one signalling section.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>ConditionSectionsClear</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ConflictingRoute -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ConflictingRoute">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#requestedRoute"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#Route"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#NonReplacement"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#Route"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteApproachLocking"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBody"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBodyProperty"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteCondition"/>
        <rdfs:comment>A table of mutually conflicting routes, that is, routes that may never be simultaneously allocated, because they utilise common track elements (Iness definition).

Before setting the requested route, the interlocking will check whether any conflicting routes are allocated.

Specialised classes are available to store the reason of the conflict if needed.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>ConflictingRoute</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#MainRoute -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#MainRoute">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#Route"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#OnSightRoute"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ShuntingRoute"/>
        <rdfs:comment>A main route for typical train operations.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>MainRoute</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#MaxRouteBodySpeed -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#MaxRouteBodySpeed">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBodyProperty"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#hasMaxSpeed_MaxRouteBodySpeed"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:comment>Maximum (signalled) line speed, i.e. the speed allowed when the signals show &apos;proceed without restrictions&apos;.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>MaxRouteBodySpeed</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#NonReplacement -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#NonReplacement">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#appliesToRoute_NonReplacement"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#Route"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#lastWheel"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#Route"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteApproachLocking"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBody"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBodyProperty"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteCondition"/>
        <rdfs:comment>To prevent a signal from closing too early. The signal is replaced only after &quot;&lt;i&gt;condition section occupied&quot; &lt;/i&gt;and &quot;&lt;i&gt;last wheel&quot; &lt;/i&gt;apply.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>lastWheel
False (default): the entry signal is replaced when the first wheel enters the next section. 

True: the entry signal is replaced only when the last wheel of the train has cleared the non-replacement section.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>NonReplacement</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#OnSightRoute -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#OnSightRoute">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#Route"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ShuntingRoute"/>
        <rdfs:comment>An on-sight route is called when track vacancy cannot be ascertained.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>OnSightRoute</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#Route -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#Route">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#appliesToRouteBody_Route"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBody"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteApproachLocking"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBody"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBodyProperty"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteCondition"/>
        <rdfs:label>Route</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteApproachLocking -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteApproachLocking">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBody"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBodyProperty"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteCondition"/>
        <rdfs:comment>The route is locked when the approach section(s) turns from vacant to occupied. 
If the DelayedLock timer is not given (or zero), the lock applies immediately.

The route approach lock can apply to:
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;an entry signal: the proceed aspect of the entry signal is locked.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;a (set of) route(s): in this case the triggering mechanism depends on the kind of route, e.g. entry speed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;a route body, in case the aspect of the entry signal or the properties of the route are irrelevant.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>RouteApproachLocking</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBody -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBody">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#hasEntry_RouteBody"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteEntry"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#hasExit_RouteBody"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteExit"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBodyProperty"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteCondition"/>
        <rdfs:comment>A route &lt;i&gt;body &lt;/i&gt;is a path with an entry and an exit. The path is a closed topological subset of the network, without any branches.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>RouteBody</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBodyProperty -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBodyProperty">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#appliesToRouteBody_RouteBodyProperty"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBody"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteCondition"/>
        <owl:disjointUnionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#MaxRouteBodySpeed"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#SectionList"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ViaLocation"/>
        </owl:disjointUnionOf>
        <rdfs:label>RouteBodyProperty</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteCondition -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteCondition">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <owl:disjointUnionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ConditionAffectingRoute"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ConditionAffectingSignal"/>
        </owl:disjointUnionOf>
        <rdfs:comment>A route condition states the conditions that must be fulfilled for a given signal &lt;i&gt;or &lt;/i&gt;route to open.
If the track asset or compound logical object&lt;font color=&quot;#ff0000&quot;&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;i&gt;is in the given state then &lt;/i&gt;the signal in this route relation is set to proceed or to the given aspect. The routeRelation is the &lt;i&gt;observer &lt;/i&gt;of the aspect and its state.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>RouteCondition</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteConflictOverlap -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteConflictOverlap">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ConflictingRoute"/>
        <rdfs:label>RouteConflictOverlap</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteConflictOverlappingTvpSections -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteConflictOverlappingTvpSections">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ConflictingRoute"/>
        <rdfs:label>RouteConflictOverlappingTvpSections</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteConvergencyConflict -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteConvergencyConflict">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ConflictingRoute"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#appliesToPointElementInPosition_RouteConvergencyConflict"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Statespace#PointElementAndPosition"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#appliesToSignal_RouteConvergencyConflict"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Signal#Signal"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#mustCheck"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Train_detection#TvpSection"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#hasDurationForCheck"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:comment>Route B conflicts with route A because a train approaching on route A may violate the gauge.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>RouteConvergencyConflict</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteEntry -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteEntry">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteExtremity"/>
        <rdfs:comment>A signal that protects the entry of the route.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>RouteEntry</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteExit -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteExit">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteExtremity"/>
        <rdfs:comment>A signal that prevents a train from entering track beyond the route body.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>RouteExit</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteExtremity -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteExtremity">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#BaseObject"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#isAssociatedWithSignal_RouteExtremity"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Signal#Signal"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointUnionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteEntry"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteExit"/>
        </owl:disjointUnionOf>
        <rdfs:comment>An abstraction of either a route entry or a route exit.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>RouteExtremity</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#SectionList -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#SectionList">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBodyProperty"/>
        <rdfs:comment>List of sections included in the route body, ordered from entry to exit.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>SectionList</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ShuntingRoute -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ShuntingRoute">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#Route"/>
        <rdfs:comment>A route for maneuvering on occupied track. TVP sections are not checked for vacancy before calling this type of route. 
If section proving is required, use the extension of this class defined in the related section proving diagram.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>ShuntingRoute</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ViaLocation -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ViaLocation">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#RouteBodyProperty"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#leadsViaLocation"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#LocationProxy"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:comment>To capture detours by defining alternative, or backup routes via a given distinctive location. Hint to the signaller to visualize via which location (track, section or signal) the train will travel.
The location proxy is placed on the topology on the track, section or signal of the route body.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>ViaLocation</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#AutoRoute -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#AutoRoute">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteProperty"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#IntermediatePointRelatedSpeedUpgrade"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteAvailableInARS"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RoutePriority"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteSetupTime"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteSpeedRestriction"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteTowardsTunnel"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteTractionType"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteWithReducedBrakingDistance"/>
        <rdfs:comment>The interlocking calls this route automatically and again, immediately after the train has cleared the route. The operator has to intervene if he wishes to call another route.
NR: autoworking
Note: When this functionality is part of the control system, use the class RouteAvailableInARS instead.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>AutoRoute</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#IntermediatePointRelatedSpeedUpgrade -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#IntermediatePointRelatedSpeedUpgrade">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteProperty"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteAvailableInARS"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RoutePriority"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteSetupTime"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteSpeedRestriction"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteTowardsTunnel"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteTractionType"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteWithReducedBrakingDistance"/>
        <rdfs:comment>This route has a point that imposes a speed reduction. Once the train has cleared the point, the speed reduction no longer applies.
de-DE: Geschwindigkeitseinschraenkung aufgrund Mittelweiche.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>IntermediatePointRelatedSpeedUpgrade</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteAvailableInARS -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteAvailableInARS">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteProperty"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RoutePriority"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteSetupTime"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteSpeedRestriction"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteTowardsTunnel"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteTractionType"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteWithReducedBrakingDistance"/>
        <rdfs:comment>This route is available in an Automatic Route Setting (ARS) system.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>RouteAvailableInARS</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RoutePriority -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RoutePriority">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteProperty"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#value_RoutePriority"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteSetupTime"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteSpeedRestriction"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteTowardsTunnel"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteTractionType"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteWithReducedBrakingDistance"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Indicates the priority of the route 
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;when there is only one route from entry to exit, priority=0&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;when there are multiple routes from entry to exit, the lowest number has highest priority. Alternative routes are numbered 1..n&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
This allows a control system to attribute priorities to route setting. Whether or not the control system auto-selects lower priority routes when no higher priority route is available, depends on national rules and regulations.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>RoutePriority</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteProperty -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteProperty">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#BaseObject"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#appliesToRoute_RouteProperty"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#Route"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:label>RouteProperty</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteSetupTime -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteSetupTime">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteProperty"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#hasSetupTime"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteSpeedRestriction"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteTowardsTunnel"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteTractionType"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteWithReducedBrakingDistance"/>
        <rdfs:comment>The typical delay between the moment the operator calls this route and the moment the entry signal opens. 
This  parameter includes the response-time of many subsystems as well as point throwing time (the position of which is often unknown beforehand). This parameter is by nature stochastic.
This parameter is useful for simulation purposes and system performance analysis.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>RouteSetupTime</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteSpeedRestriction -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteSpeedRestriction">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteProperty"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#hasSpeedRestriction"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteTowardsTunnel"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteTractionType"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteWithReducedBrakingDistance"/>
        <rdfs:comment>Speed restriction resulting from external constraints that cannot be deduced from the elements situated along or associated with this route. For instance noise reduction or simplification of speed profiles.
Not to be used for speed restriction due to reduced braking distance. Use the class &lt;a href=&quot;$element://{74A6B407-1140-41ae-B7DB-608B70FD2999}&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#0000ff&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Route With Reduced Braking Distance&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; instead.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>RouteSpeedRestriction</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteTowardsTunnel -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteTowardsTunnel">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteProperty"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteTractionType"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteWithReducedBrakingDistance"/>
        <rdfs:label>RouteTowardsTunnel</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteTractionType -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteTractionType">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteProperty"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#isSuitableForTractionType"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteWithReducedBrakingDistance"/>
        <rdfs:comment>The route is suitable for the given type of traction.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>RouteTractionType</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteWithReducedBrakingDistance -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteWithReducedBrakingDistance">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#RouteProperty"/>
        <rdfs:comment>The distance to the closed signal of this route is lower than usual, resulting in a shorter braking distance. This in turn can be signalled to the driver with a specific sequence of aspects (UK, NL, FR solution, pre-annonce) or an extra light (DE solution, Zusatzlicht).</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>RouteWithReducedBrakingDistance</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#ShuntingRouteSectionProving -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#ShuntingRouteSectionProving">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Route_properties#appliesToShuntingRoute"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route#ShuntingRoute"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:comment>A shunting route can normally be activated even if one or more sections are not proven vacant. This class selects which sections must be proven vacant.
If no sections are needed vacant no ShuntingRouteSectionProving instance is created.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>ShuntingRouteSectionProving</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#DirectionAuthorityDependentOverlap -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#DirectionAuthorityDependentOverlap">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#appliesToBlockElement"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Assets/Block_system#BlockElement"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#appliesToOverlap_DirectionAuthorityDependentOverlap"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#Overlap"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#SafetyDistance"/>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#SwingingOverlap"/>
        <rdfs:comment>The overlap can only be activated when the block accepts the direction in which the route and thus the overlap are set.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>DirectionAuthorityDependentOverlap</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#DistanceToDangerpoint -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#DistanceToDangerpoint">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#SafetyDistance"/>
        <rdfs:comment>The dangerpoint defines the position beyond the exit signal up to where a train is likely to be safe.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>DistanceToDangerpoint</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#NotUpgradeableSpeedRestriction -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#NotUpgradeableSpeedRestriction">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#BaseObject"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#appliesToOverlap_NotUpgradeableSpeedRestriction"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#Overlap"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#OverlapRelease"/>
        <rdfs:comment>An overlap can cause a speed restriction in the approach route. 
This class lists the overlaps for which the speed isn&apos;t upgraded when the exit signal opens.
For an overlap not in the list, the IL lifts the speed restriction when the exit signal opens.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>NotUpgradeableSpeedRestriction</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#Overlap -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#Overlap">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#SafetyDistance"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#overlapRelease"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#OverlapRelease"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:label>Overlap</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#OverlapRelease -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#OverlapRelease">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#BaseObject"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#overlapReleaseCondition"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:comment>Unlocks the elements in the overlap.
The IL may release the overlap in the following situations:
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When the approaching train &lt;i&gt;has plausibly stopped&lt;/i&gt; before the exit signal. In this case, the overlap release is delayed by a given duration: the timer is triggered when the train occupies or vacates a given section.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When the approaching train &lt;i&gt;positively confirms to have stopped&lt;/i&gt; (e.g. by means of an ETCS position report). In this case, the release is immediate or with a short delay.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>OverlapRelease</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#SafetyDistance -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#SafetyDistance">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#isLocatedAt_SafetyDistance"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#hasDesignSlope_SafetyDistance"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#hasMinimalLength"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <owl:disjointWith rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#SwingingOverlap"/>
        <owl:disjointUnionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#DistanceToDangerpoint"/>
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#Overlap"/>
        </owl:disjointUnionOf>
        <rdfs:comment>The safety distance must be specialised into an (ETCS) overlap or a distance to dangerpoint.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>SafetyDistance</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#SwingingOverlap -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#SwingingOverlap">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#ConfiguredBaseObject"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#appliesToOverlap_SwingingOverlap"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Route/Safety_distance#Overlap"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:comment>An overlap section may, even though locked, be swung away from a conflicting route to provide a full-length overlap (source: INESS)
The swinging overlap typically contains a facing point (de-DE: Ruderweiche). This implies that 
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;there are two possible overlaps associated with the closed exit signal and&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the signaller can swing the overlap between left and right (normal and reverse).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
The swinging overlap must point to two limiting train detectors.
National rules and regulations govern when and how the facing point(s) can be thrown.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>SwingingOverlap</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Speed_profiles#FreightTrain -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Speed_profiles#FreightTrain">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Signalling/Speed_profiles#TrainCategory"/>
        <rdfs:label>FreightTrain</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


