    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Geo_information#scheme_RelationSetType_EAID_8CDED51F_03A7_4e8e_8C52_7D97F3DB296A -->

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Geo_information#scheme_RelationSetType_EAID_8CDED51F_03A7_4e8e_8C52_7D97F3DB296A">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#ConceptScheme"/>
        <rdfs:comment>cut
Node created to split a linear element considered too long for practical purposes.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>legacy
Node created e.g. at import from a classical node-edge model, for seamless tracing of legacy graphs.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>temporaryConnection
Node created to split or carve out a part of the topology. 
Allows creating independent topologies to be (re-)engineered in parallel and merged back after completion.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>RelationSetType</rdfs:label>
    </owl:NamedIndividual>
    


