    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/National_implementations/NR/Working_safety#scheme_LockoutDeviceTypes_EAID_694D2FDE_D466_4a06_AA5E_055150FBFF1E -->

    <owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/National_implementations/NR/Working_safety#scheme_LockoutDeviceTypes_EAID_694D2FDE_D466_4a06_AA5E_055150FBFF1E">
        <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#ConceptScheme"/>
        <rdfs:comment>d
Disallows main route setting into the lockout area but shunting movements are allowed.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>e
Similar to type k except that the key is in possession of platform staff and sometimes siding staff.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>k
Removing the captive key prevents train movements in both directions.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>o
Like type &quot;k&quot; except that authorised staff keeps the keys that activate the lockout devices in a lockout area.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>p
Protects line-side workers, patrol men, by preventing train movement in the wrong direction.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:comment>switchLock
Old type of lockout device.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>LockoutDeviceTypes</rdfs:label>
    </owl:NamedIndividual>
    


